rows.text: Private vehicles from the early 1970's until the mid 1980's
Motorcycles (e.g., FBA, FBB, and so on); started at the end of December 2005. The current prefix being issued is FBP.
File:Singapore 1990 rear vehicle registration plate of a blue Hyundai vehicle (cropped).jpg
Light Goods vehicles (class 3) (e.g., GBA - GBG(Apr 2017); introduced from the year 2010, after GZ. The current prefix being issued is GBJ.

Private operator buses (PA, PB, PC, PD, PH, PZ were used to separate private buses, private hire vehicles, and so on, but later on all private hire vehicles were issued with PA and PC plates). The current prefix being issued is PD.
Company vehicles (no longer issued – company cars are now issued with "S" series number plates like private cars). Conflict with Sarawak series.
Private vehicles, also formal number plate series. The current prefix being issued is SMP. Older vintage series with two letters prefix conflict with some Sabah series.

Taxis or street hire vehicles such as Singapore-Johore Express, former SBS buses operating Sentosa and Airport services (AIRBUS) and Singapore Explorer Trolley - City Sightseeing buses. The current prefix being issued is SHF.
Trailers. The current prefix being issued is TRD.
Engineering plant vehicles (Class 5), some registered Jeeps and Rovers. The current prefix being issued is WD. Conflict with some newer extended Kuala Lumpur series.
Very heavy goods vehicles (Class 5/prime movers) not constructed to carry any load. The current prefix being issued is XE.
Heavy goods vehicles (class 3/4) The current prefix being issued is YQ.
